{"componentChunkName":"component---src-components-blog-post-jsx","path":"/love2d-on-wsl/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Setting up LÃ¶ve2D on WSL is fairly simple and similar to the set up on\nwindows by itself. This guide assumes that you already have WSL installed and your\nenvironment setup. I am using WSL 2 for this and as of writing this guide, this\nis only available if you use windows insider preview to get\nthe nightly build of windows.</p>\n<h2>Setting it up on Windows</h2>\n<p>First, go to <a href=\"http://love2d.org\">love2d.org</a> to download the necessary\ninstaller. In my case I clicked on the <em>64-bit installer.</em></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 650px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/69f8cfa77e66da95e66f11ebc1a1aa1d/a6ec4/love-install-link.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 87.11656441717791%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"LÃ¶ve2D Installation Link\"\n        title=\"LÃ¶ve2D Installation Link\"\n        src=\"/static/69f8cfa77e66da95e66f11ebc1a1aa1d/a6d36/love-install-link.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/69f8cfa77e66da95e66f11ebc1a1aa1d/222b7/love-install-link.png 163w,\n/static/69f8cfa77e66da95e66f11ebc1a1aa1d/ff46a/love-install-link.png 325w,\n/static/69f8cfa77e66da95e66f11ebc1a1aa1d/a6d36/love-install-link.png 650w,\n/static/69f8cfa77e66da95e66f11ebc1a1aa1d/e548f/love-install-link.png 975w,\n/static/69f8cfa77e66da95e66f11ebc1a1aa1d/3c492/love-install-link.png 1300w,\n/static/69f8cfa77e66da95e66f11ebc1a1aa1d/a6ec4/love-install-link.png 1438w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>I followed the installer so that the application was installed on the system. You\ncan test that this is working by typing \"love\" into the windows search bar and\nclicking on the application. A stock GIF of a ballon ðŸŽˆ should pop up in the love\ngame window.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 650px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9f732943f80fdf146bdfd3a370301d67/a4262/environment-variables-popup.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 110.42944785276075%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Windows Environment Variables\"\n        title=\"Windows Environment Variables\"\n        src=\"/static/9f732943f80fdf146bdfd3a370301d67/a6d36/environment-variables-popup.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9f732943f80fdf146bdfd3a370301d67/222b7/environment-variables-popup.png 163w,\n/static/9f732943f80fdf146bdfd3a370301d67/ff46a/environment-variables-popup.png 325w,\n/static/9f732943f80fdf146bdfd3a370301d67/a6d36/environment-variables-popup.png 650w,\n/static/9f732943f80fdf146bdfd3a370301d67/a4262/environment-variables-popup.png 814w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Before transitioning over to WSL you need to add love to your environment\nvariables.\nIn the windows search bar type <em>edit the system environment variables</em> and open\nthe dialog window that pops up.</p>\n<p>If this does not work go the control panel and manually search for this window</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 650px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/037497c7388e58544471ecf1ddb4baef/4c7dc/love-default.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 79.14110429447852%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"LÃ¶ve2D Default Popup\"\n        title=\"LÃ¶ve2D Default Popup\"\n        src=\"/static/037497c7388e58544471ecf1ddb4baef/a6d36/love-default.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/037497c7388e58544471ecf1ddb4baef/222b7/love-default.png 163w,\n/static/037497c7388e58544471ecf1ddb4baef/ff46a/love-default.png 325w,\n/static/037497c7388e58544471ecf1ddb4baef/a6d36/love-default.png 650w,\n/static/037497c7388e58544471ecf1ddb4baef/e548f/love-default.png 975w,\n/static/037497c7388e58544471ecf1ddb4baef/3c492/love-default.png 1300w,\n/static/037497c7388e58544471ecf1ddb4baef/4c7dc/love-default.png 1599w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>From here click on environment variables and add the <em>.exe</em> for LÃ¶ve2D to your path.\nFor me this was located at <strong>C:/Program Files/LOVE</strong> but this could vary depending\non what options you picked during installation</p>\n<p>You can test this by opening up command prompt and typing <code class=\"abyss grvsc-mm-tJ07fR\" data-language=\"bash\" data-index=\"0\"><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-1 grvsc-tJ07fR-1\">love</span></code> into the shell.\nThis should load the balloon GIF shown above. Once this is working you are ready\nto transition to WSL.</p>\n<h2>Setting it up on WSL</h2>\n<p>Open up WSL in your desired method</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Typing WSL into run.exe</li>\n<li>Typing <code class=\"abyss grvsc-mm-tJ07fR\" data-language=\"bash\" data-index=\"1\"><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-1 grvsc-tJ07fR-1\">wsl</span></code> in command prompt</li>\n<li>Using another terminal emulator</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Now in WSL2, you can run windows <em>exe's</em> by typing in the name of the entire exe.\nHowever, it needs to be on your path for it to work. An example of this is to type\n<code class=\"abyss grvsc-mm-tJ07fR\" data-language=\"bash\" data-index=\"2\"><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-1 grvsc-tJ07fR-1\">explorer.exe</span></code> to open up the windows file explorer</p>\n<p>Typing <code class=\"abyss grvsc-mm-tJ07fR\" data-language=\"bash\" data-index=\"3\"><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-1 grvsc-tJ07fR-1\">explorer.exe </span><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-15 grvsc-tJ07fR-11\">.</span></code> in WSL will open the windows file explorer in the WSL\nfile system</p>\n<p>So from WSL, you can type <code class=\"abyss grvsc-mm-tJ07fR\" data-language=\"bash\" data-index=\"4\"><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-1 grvsc-tJ07fR-1\">love.exe</span></code> to run LÃ¶ve2D from within WSL. To make the\ndevelopment process similar to Linux/Unix you can make an alias to it. Personally,\nI don't like typing out the <em>.exe</em> every time so I have an alias for <code class=\"abyss grvsc-mm-tJ07fR\" data-language=\"bash\" data-index=\"5\"><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-1 grvsc-tJ07fR-1\">love</span></code>. The below\nscript will add the alias to your bashrc and source it.</p>\n<pre class=\"grvsc-container abyss grvsc-mm-tJ07fR\" data-language=\"bash\" data-index=\"0\"><code class=\"grvsc-code\"><span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-1 grvsc-tJ07fR-1\">$ </span><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-15 grvsc-tJ07fR-11\">echo</span><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-1 grvsc-tJ07fR-1\"> </span><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-11 grvsc-tJ07fR-8\">&quot;alias love=&#39;love.exe&#39;&quot;</span><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-1 grvsc-tJ07fR-1\"> </span><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-7 grvsc-tJ07fR-15\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-1 grvsc-tJ07fR-1\"> </span><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-7 grvsc-tJ07fR-15\">~</span><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-1 grvsc-tJ07fR-1\">/.bashrc</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"grvsc-line\"><span class=\"grvsc-source\"><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-1 grvsc-tJ07fR-1\">$ </span><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-15 grvsc-tJ07fR-11\">source</span><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-1 grvsc-tJ07fR-1\"> </span><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-7 grvsc-tJ07fR-15\">~</span><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-1 grvsc-tJ07fR-1\">/.bashrc</span></span></span></code></pre>\n<p>If you are using a different shell or would prefer to put your aliases somewhere\nelse you can write it in manually.</p>\n<p>Now you should be able to simply type <code class=\"abyss grvsc-mm-tJ07fR\" data-language=\"bash\" data-index=\"6\"><span class=\"grvsc-t9ljLd-1 grvsc-tJ07fR-1\">love</span></code> in your terminal to run LÃ¶ve2D. You\nare ready to develop and prototype your own games!! ðŸŽ®</p>\n<style class=\"grvsc-styles\">\n  .grvsc-container {\n    overflow: auto;\n    position: relative;\n    -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;\n    padding-top: 1rem;\n    padding-top: var(--grvsc-padding-top, var(--grvsc-padding-v, 1rem));\n    padding-bottom: 1rem;\n    padding-bottom: var(--grvsc-padding-bottom, var(--grvsc-padding-v, 1rem));\n    border-radius: 8px;\n    border-radius: var(--grvsc-border-radius, 8px);\n    font-feature-settings: normal;\n    line-height: 1.4;\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-code {\n    display: table;\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-line {\n    display: table-row;\n    box-sizing: border-box;\n    width: 100%;\n    position: relative;\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-line > * {\n    position: relative;\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-gutter-pad {\n    display: table-cell;\n    padding-left: 0.75rem;\n    padding-left: calc(var(--grvsc-padding-left, var(--grvsc-padding-h, 1.5rem)) / 2);\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-gutter {\n    display: table-cell;\n    -webkit-user-select: none;\n    -moz-user-select: none;\n    user-select: none;\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-gutter::before {\n    content: attr(data-content);\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-source {\n    display: table-cell;\n    padding-left: 1.5rem;\n    padding-left: var(--grvsc-padding-left, var(--grvsc-padding-h, 1.5rem));\n    padding-right: 1.5rem;\n    padding-right: var(--grvsc-padding-right, var(--grvsc-padding-h, 1.5rem));\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-source:empty::after {\n    content: ' ';\n    -webkit-user-select: none;\n    -moz-user-select: none;\n    user-select: none;\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-gutter + .grvsc-source {\n    padding-left: 0.75rem;\n    padding-left: calc(var(--grvsc-padding-left, var(--grvsc-padding-h, 1.5rem)) / 2);\n  }\n  \n  /* Line transformer styles */\n  \n  .grvsc-has-line-highlighting > .grvsc-code > .grvsc-line::before {\n    content: ' ';\n    position: absolute;\n    width: 100%;\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-line-diff-add::before {\n    background-color: var(--grvsc-line-diff-add-background-color, rgba(0, 255, 60, 0.2));\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-line-diff-del::before {\n    background-color: var(--grvsc-line-diff-del-background-color, rgba(255, 0, 20, 0.2));\n  }\n  \n  .grvsc-line-number {\n    padding: 0 2px;\n    text-align: right;\n    opacity: 0.7;\n  }\n  \n  .abyss { background-color: #000c18; }\n  .abyss .grvsc-t9ljLd-1 { color: #6688CC; }\n  .abyss .grvsc-t9ljLd-15 { color: #9966B8; }\n  .abyss .grvsc-t9ljLd-11 { color: #22AA44; }\n  .abyss .grvsc-t9ljLd-7 { color: #225588; }\n  .abyss .grvsc-line-highlighted::before {\n    background-color: var(--grvsc-line-highlighted-backgr